—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2021-12-28-nushell_0_42.mdظ@4976fdcf7f37f23cda91dda4fa9e4c3221f57561c6765dc4996b751d595b6231³title: Nushell 0.42‘±Engine-q progressع€At this point, we're now 100% focused on getting engine-q done. Over 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/pulls?page=1&q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed] 120 PRs
 have been merged into engine-q since the last Nushell release and another 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/reedline/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed] 20 PRs in reedline
.
Engine-q is now able to be used as a standalone shell. It includes the full set of dataframe functionality and most of the nushell commands. We aren't yet making nightly builds available, but you should be able to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q] clone and build engine-q
 on your machine in the same way you might grab the latest Nushell. As you try out engine-q, also give a read over the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/522] in-progress breaking change list
, as it shows where the new engine will differ from Nushell's current engine.
’گگع¼Title: title: Nushell 0.42
Path: Engine-q progress
Content:
At this point, we're now 100% focused on getting engine-q done. Over 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/pulls?page=1&q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed] 120 PRs
 have been merged into engine-q since the last Nushell release and another 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/reedline/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed] 20 PRs in reedline
.
Engine-q is now able to be used as a standalone shell. It includes the full set of dataframe functionality and most of the nushell commands. We aren't yet making nightly builds available, but you should be able to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q] clone and build engine-q
 on your machine in the same way you might grab the latest Nushell. As you try out engine-q, also give a read over the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/522] in-progress breaking change list
, as it shows where the new engine will differ from Nushell's current engine.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2021-12-28-nushell_0_42.mdظ@7a62018dd08f0d8bd8aaac460f331fe752a0307c3e6427e0185ec34cfdf10de2³title: Nushell 0.42‘¯Looking forwardع‚There are still 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/242] some commands left to port
 if you'd like to jump in and give porting a try. If you're interested, you can also help us by testing out engine-q itself as a shell and report your experiences with it. And of course, come join us on the 
[link: https://discord.gg/NtAbbGn] discord
. We'd be happy to show you around.
’گگع¼Title: title: Nushell 0.42
Path: Looking forward
Content:
There are still 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/242] some commands left to port
 if you'd like to jump in and give porting a try. If you're interested, you can also help us by testing out engine-q itself as a shell and report your experiences with it. And of course, come join us on the 
[link: https://discord.gg/NtAbbGn] discord
. We'd be happy to show you around.
